Program: Great Lives
Title: Nero
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b00pkbmf
Last Broadcast Date: Fri 29 Sep 2017
Matthew Parris presents the biographical series in which his guests choose someone who has inspired their lives. Christopher Biggins champions the life of the Roman Emperor Nero, a man whose modest talent for poetry was overshadowed by his debauchery, extravagance and tyranny.